Two bare attribute operands under an ORDERING comparison (`span.a > span.b`)
numeric-coerce BOTH sides via toFloat64OrNull. Before the fix this fell through
to a raw Map(String,String) compare — lexicographic, so `'10' > '5'` was false.
Equality (`=`/`!=`) deliberately stays a string compare; only ordering implies
numeric intent on two attributes.

-- query.traceql --
{ span.a > span.b }
-- sql --
SELECT * FROM `otel_traces` WHERE (toFloat64OrNull(`SpanAttributes`[?]) > toFloat64OrNull(`SpanAttributes`[?]))
-- chplan --
Filter predicate=(toFloat64OrNull(SpanAttributes["a"]) > toFloat64OrNull(SpanAttributes["b"]))
  Scan(otel_traces)
-- args --
[0] string = "a"
[1] string = "b"
